01/08/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- Troops killed two members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) on Thursday (July 31st) in the eastern province of Tunceli, local media reported. 
In a separate incident Thursday, a PKK ambush reportedly killed one Turkish soldier and wounded two others in the central city of Sivas. 
The PKK is listed as a terrorist organisation by most of the international community, including the United States and the EU. 
(Hurriyet - 01/08/08, Hurriyet, Dogan news agency, Anadolu news agency, CNN Turk - 31/07/08)
